This is boiler-plate code for an open-world first-person shooter game.
These scripts work with Unity3D editor 5.6.1f1. Ubuntu link below.
https://forum.unity3d.com/threads/unity-on-linux-release-notes-and-known-issues.350256/

Vision: Provide first-person shooter roleplaying gameplay similar to the recent
installments of The Elder Scrolls and Fallout series, albeit with the addition
of couch-multiplayer coop.

Strategy:
I aim to assemble a minimally-viable feature-complete version of the game.
I then aim to improve the user-experience by revisiting existing features.
After this stage, my aim will be to provide compelling assets to immerse the
player in a rich game world.

Tentative roadmap:

Refactor
  -Use polymorphism for Items.
  -Use polymorphism for menus.
  -Use polymorphism for Actor
  -Inventory component to contain inventory logic.
  -Slot component to contain ability/item use logic.
  -Stats component to contain RPG stats logic

React to feedback:
  -Determine format for Models/Animation
  -Determine Priority of existing V1.0 Goals
  -Determine new V1.0 Goals.

